  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The approach of the Shanghai Maritime University is similar to the implementations at the University in Singapore, although it is addressing strategic decisionmaking problems regarding the design of container terminals.",
    "Their digital twin implementation has been described in the interview with the Centre of Excellence in Modelling and Simulation for Next Generation Ports and uses different types of simulation-based optimizations for planning the future port in Singapore, optimizing the layout and overall throughput (Li et al. 2021b).",
    "Thereby, the entire port, with land and sea side on a broad level and details such as crane models, different routes and work steps of everything that can move in the terminal are simulated.",
    "Another feature of the Singapore implementation is the additional scope on vehicle charging for automated battery-powered vehicles in the terminal.",
    "Although using extensive simulation, a strict digital twin is not implemented due to the lack of (near) real-time data being included."
  ],
